<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62d1e070-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s4212"><num value="4212">§ 4212.</num><heading> Training and technical assistance</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated for assistance for a national organization representing Native American housing interests for providing training and technical assistance to Indian housing authorities and tribally designated housing entities such sums as may be necessary for each of fiscal years 2009 through 2013.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id62d1e071-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/104/330/tVII/s703">Pub. L. 104–330, title VII, § 703</ref>, <date date="1996-10-26">Oct. 26, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/4051">110 Stat. 4051</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/107/292/s2/c">Pub. L. 107–292, § 2(c)</ref>, <date date="2002-11-13">Nov. 13, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/2053">116 Stat. 2053</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/110/411/tVII/s701/c">Pub. L. 110–411, title VII, § 701(c)</ref>, <date date="2008-10-14">Oct. 14, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/4334">122 Stat. 4334</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id62d1e072-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">
